**3.1 Victory Lap / “If It Makes Millions, That’s Also My Problem” Clause**
If the Software, by accident or genius, solves a **multi-million-dollar** problem, prints money, saves the company, wins the war, lands the contract, cures your pager duty, or otherwise turns your life into a highlight reel—then, spiritually speaking, that is **a me-problem**: I deserve disproportionate credit, excessive praise, and at least one dramatic “remember the name” moment.
